From: Luca Weiss <luca.weiss@fairphone.com>
Date: Fri, 25 Apr 2025 14:12:55 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] clk: qcom: camcc-sm6350: Add *_wait_val values for GDSCs
References: bsc#1234429
Patch-mainline: 6.12.34
Git-commit: e7b1c13280ad866f3b935f6c658713c41db61635

[ Upstream commit e7b1c13280ad866f3b935f6c658713c41db61635 ]

Compared to the msm-4.19 driver the mainline GDSC driver always sets the
bits for en_rest, en_few & clk_dis, and if those values are not set
per-GDSC in the respective driver then the default value from the GDSC
driver is used. The downstream driver only conditionally sets
clk_dis_wait_val if qcom,clk-dis-wait-val is given in devicetree.

Correct this situation by explicitly setting those values. For all GDSCs
the reset value of those bits are used.

Fixes: 80f5451d9a7c ("clk: qcom: Add camera clock controller driver for SM6350")
Signed-off-by: Luca Weiss <luca.weiss@fairphone.com>
Reviewed-by: Taniya Das <quic_tdas@quicinc.com>
